## Design observation #3 ŌĆö Theme write asymmetry

`frontend/src/lib/themes/store.svelte.ts:68-82` ŌĆö `setTheme()` calls
`applyThemeToDom()` + `saveStoredTheme()` (localStorage). No PATCH.

`frontend/src/lib/themes/ThemePicker.svelte:14-20` ŌĆö ThemePicker calls
only `setTheme()` from this store; it does NOT PATCH `/api/preferences`.

`frontend/src/lib/components/settings/sections/DefaultsSection.svelte:108-122`
ŌĆö Defaults' theme handler calls both `setTheme()` AND `patchField({theme:next})`.

The audit text says "Asymmetry is intentional per spec but means Appearance
changes don't persist to DB." Spec at docs/behavior/preferences.md:64
confirms: Defaults additionally PATCHes `/api/preferences`. Spec is silent
on Appearance writing to DB.

Verdict: STILL_OPEN as design observation. The audit acknowledges
intentionality. Severity minor.

## Pre-dispatch signal ŌĆö pytest route-naming failures

Investigation: `grep -rn "route_name\|operation_id\|naming" tests/` returned
no naming-convention test. preferences.py and reorg.py route function names
(`get_preferences`, `patch_preferences`, `get_avatar`, ...; `merge_session`,
`split_session`, `move_message`, `list_reorg_audits`, `undo_reorg_audit`)
are unique within their files and do not collide across the app's routers
inspected via `grep`. No `name=` argument is used on `@router.<verb>`
decorators in either file.

Per runbook directive: "Run pytest / mypy / lints. Read tests, don't run
them." ŌĆö I cannot independently verify the pytest failure mode. The tests at
tests/test_preferences_*.py and tests/test_reorg_api.py read cleanly and
make no obvious naming-related assertions. If the failure exists, it is not
a route-naming issue surfaced by static reading; it may be a fixture/plugin
issue (asyncio_mode=auto config in pyproject.toml seems standard).

Recommendation: surface this signal to the executor brief for finding #4
(test coverage) and let the executor confirm/diagnose at test-implementation
time. No standalone STILL_OPEN finding emitted for this signal.

